[I was another British scientist working at the Institute Evandro Chagas at the mouth of the Amazon in those early days, and a contemporary of Ralph's. He was a good friend and excellent scientist, who received many well-deserved honours for his important work on leishmaniasis.

References:
LAINSON, R.; J. J. SHAW; F. T. SILVEIRA; A. A. A. SOUZA; R. R. BRAGA & E. A. Y. ISHIKAWA, 1994. The dermal leishmaniases of Brazil, with special reference to the eco-epidemiology of the disease in Amazonia. Mem. Inst. Oswaldo Cruz 89:435-443.

LAINSON, R. & J. J. SHAW, 1992. A brief history of the genus _Leishmania_ (Protozoa: Kinetoplastida) in the Americas, with particular reference to Amazonian Brazil. Ciencia Cultura, 44:94-106.
- Mod.JW

